[
    {
        "content": "<p>Why do some lemmas for casting to dual orders like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=LT.lt.dual#doc\">docs#LT.lt.dual</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsLUB.dual#doc\">docs#IsLUB.dual</a>, etc. use <code>.dual</code>, while others like <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=IsMin.toDual#doc\">docs#IsMin.toDual</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=CovBy.toDual#doc\">docs#CovBy.toDual</a>, use <code>.toDual</code>?</p>",
        "id": 467334422,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725388467
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is this just a naming inconsistency, or is there some deeper reason?</p>",
        "id": 467334458,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725388485
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The deeper reason is that those lemmas are not just an application of <code>toDual</code> everywhere. Eg a set <code>s : Set α</code> becomes <code>ofDual ⁻¹' s : Set αᵒᵈ</code>, not <code>toDual '' s : Set αᵒᵈ</code>.</p>",
        "id": 467334745,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1725388606
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What about <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Order.isSuccLimit.dual#doc\">docs#Order.isSuccLimit.dual</a> ? That seems like a straightforward application of <code>toDual</code> everywhere.</p>",
        "id": 467339338,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725389943
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Your link 404s</p>",
        "id": 467345098,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1725392150
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Order.isSuccLimit.dual#doc\">docs#Order.isSuccLimit.dual</a> is misnamed. The inside namespace should be<code>IsSuccLimit</code></p>",
        "id": 467345219,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1725392200
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Should it also be <code>.toDual</code>?</p>",
        "id": 467345274,
        "sender_full_name": "Violeta Hernández",
        "timestamp": 1725392233
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think it could also reasonably be called <code>.toDual</code>, but the general pattern is to make <code>.dual</code> be the lemma that people want to use when dualising, to avoid them having to think about whether to use <code>toDual</code> or <code>ofDual</code></p>",
        "id": 467345324,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1725392265
    }
]